A
\int A e^{-\alpha^2 s^2}\, ds = -1
\int\limits_0^\infty  {A{e^{ - {{\left( {\alpha s} \right)}^2}}}ds =  - 1} 
\alpha s = u
\int\limits_0^\infty  {A{e^{ - {u^2}}}\frac{{du}}{\alpha } =  - 1} 
\frac{A}{\alpha }\frac{{\sqrt \pi  }}{2} =  - 1
A\sqrt \pi   =  - 2\alpha 
\int {A{e^{ - {\alpha ^2}{s^2}}}ds} 
